which comprise, for example,
the rectum, the urinary bladder

00:02:37.840 --> 00:02:39.600
in both males and females,

00:02:39.600 --> 00:02:45.040
and in the female body,
also looks after

00:02:45.040 --> 00:02:50.480
the functioning of the reproductive organs,
such as the uterus, the fallopian tubes.

00:02:50.480 --> 00:02:52.560
As we had also said
during the first episode,

00:02:52.560 --> 00:02:56.480
that the autonomic nervous system,
comprising two components,

00:02:56.480 --> 00:02:59.600
the parasympathetic and the sympathetic,

00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:03.520
it's like this: the origin is in the brain,
it's like an inverted tree.

00:03:03.520 --> 00:03:06.240
We had spoken about that,
with roots in the brain

00:03:06.240 --> 00:03:08.880
and the branches
come downwards.

00:03:08.880 --> 00:03:13.280
So, the parasympathetic and the sympathetic
work very close to each other.

00:03:13.280 --> 00:03:15.280
They are the two main components of it,

00:03:15.280 --> 00:03:19.520
and one thing that we should remember,
even as we look at these chakras,

00:03:19.520 --> 00:03:22.240
the first energy center,
which we dealt with before,

00:03:22.240 --> 00:03:26.160
the second and the third energy centers
which we are going to talk about today,

00:03:26.160 --> 00:03:28.560
and the energy centers above that,

00:03:28.560 --> 00:03:32.000
they all function as one unit.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:34.240
It's a holistic unit.

00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:37.440
If we start adopting a kind of a
Cartesian frame of approach,

00:03:37.440 --> 00:03:40.160
then the audience would be misinformed,

00:03:40.160 --> 00:03:43.680
