00:04:27.520 --> 00:04:30.560
that it may have with
the nervous system.

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:34.400
Before we go to the
third energy center,

00:04:35.040 --> 00:04:37.360
which is the Nabhi or
the Manipura chakra,

00:04:37.360 --> 00:04:40.320
and the corresponding plexus,

00:04:40.320 --> 00:04:46.720
the Void is probably one of the most
intriguing and interesting aspects

00:04:46.720 --> 00:04:50.880
of the entire subtle system
and also how it corresponds

00:04:50.880 --> 00:04:52.720
to neuroanatomy.

00:04:52.720 --> 00:04:57.520
Now, there is a lot of research
that has happened,

00:04:57.520 --> 00:05:02.560
particularly in the past century,
more so in the past 30-40 years,

00:05:02.560 --> 00:05:07.600
that seems to suggest that
the autonomic nervous system

00:05:07.600 --> 00:05:12.400
comprises not two,
but three components.

00:05:12.400 --> 00:05:17.600
You have the parasympathetic component,
as is represented by the vagus nerve

00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:18.960
for the most part.

00:05:18.960 --> 00:05:22.560
You have the sympathetic component,
which is the two chains

00:05:22.560 --> 00:05:27.040
of sympathetic ganglia 
that run close

00:05:27.040 --> 00:05:29.440
to the vertebral column outside of it.

00:05:29.440 --> 00:05:32.000
And then there is, hold your breath,

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:37.600
it's called the enteric nervous system,
the ENS.

00:05:37.600 --> 00:05:44.080
And the ENS is now thought to be
a third, very important,

00:05:44.080 --> 00:05:50.480
completely independent
component of the autonomic nervous system.

00:05:50.480 --> 00:05:56.240
And the reason for this is that
it has its own governing system

00:05:56.240 --> 00:06:00.400
that is not controlled
directly from the brain.

00:06:00.400 --> 00:06:03.920
There are innervations,
there is a crosstalk,

00:06:03.920 --> 00:06:08.320
but the way it functions is that
you have these nerves

00:06:08.320 --> 00:06:12.560
that are present
throughout the gut.

00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:16.960
Gut starts from
the esophagus

00:06:16.960 --> 00:06:20.000
right up to the rectum
and the anal canal.

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:25.040
The entire gut, but within
the abdominal cavity, you could say,

00:06:25.040 --> 00:06:30.000
you have this nervous system
which has its innervations,

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:37.200
which has its connections
within the walls of the entire gut.

00:06:37.200 --> 00:06:40.960
And through neurotransmitters,

00:06:41.520 --> 00:06:46.480
through nerve impulses,
through these kinds of neurohormones,

00:06:46.480 --> 00:06:51.920
it controls in a relatively
independent fashion

00:06:51.920 --> 00:06:54.880
the functioning of the entire gut.

00:06:54.880 --> 00:06:56.880
So, what does that mean?

00:06:56.880 --> 00:07:02.720
When we eat something,
you chew, you masticate,

00:07:02.720 --> 00:07:04.880
and then you swallow.

00:07:04.880 --> 00:07:10.400
When you swallow, that begins the process,
or what enables swallowing,

00:07:10.400 --> 00:07:12.960
as we call it, is peristalsis.

00:07:12.960 --> 00:07:16.560
Peristalsis is this movement
of the gut that allows food

00:07:16.560 --> 00:07:22.000
to propel from point A to point B,
to point C, point D, all the way down,

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:27.280
and that is how the nutrients
are absorbed from what we eat

00:07:27.840 --> 00:07:32.720
in our food, or whatever we drink,
is absorbed.

00:07:32.720 --> 00:07:35.760
So, that is possible
because of peristalsis.

00:07:35.760 --> 00:07:44.880
Peristalsis is possible,
this movement of the muscles of the gut,

00:07:44.880 --> 00:07:49.200
is possible because, again,
we had spoken the last time around,

00:07:49.200 --> 00:07:53.520
of electrical impulses that are created
within the nervous system.

00:07:53.520 --> 00:07:55.360
That's what the nervous system is;

00:07:55.360 --> 00:07:56.960
it's an electrical system.

00:07:56.960 --> 00:08:00.800
So, these impulses that are created
within the gut

00:08:00.800 --> 00:08:04.880
are a function of the
enteric nervous system.

00:08:04.880 --> 00:08:08.080
So, this ENS, or the enteric
nervous system,

00:08:08.080 --> 00:08:11.040
is now considered to be
an independent unit.

00:08:11.040 --> 00:08:15.280
If we look at the subtle system,
now, this comes to the relationship

00:08:15.280 --> 00:08:19.040
with the autonomous nervous system,
to answer your question.

00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:22.800
If you look at a graph
of the subtle system

00:08:22.800 --> 00:08:27.760
that we have in our body,
you notice that it starts from here,

00:08:27.760 --> 00:08:32.000
or rather, it starts
from the bottom,

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:35.040
and it stops at the
second energy center,

00:08:35.040 --> 00:08:39.680
and then from the second energy center
to the fourth energy center,

00:08:39.680 --> 00:08:43.360
it's like you can see a dot, dot, dot,
dotted kind of a line.

00:08:43.360 --> 00:08:48.560
And that, from a spiritual point of view,
is considered a Void.

00:08:48.560 --> 00:08:52.880
Void is nothingness,
that there is nothing there.

00:08:52.880 --> 00:08:59.120
And that is extraordinarily interesting
because the parasympathetic nervous system,

00:08:59.120 --> 00:09:04.400
it gets a little technical, but it is
of immense consequence

00:09:04.400 --> 00:09:07.120
and great interest.

00:09:07.120 --> 00:09:13.760
So, the parasympathetic nervous system
consists of two sources of outflows,

00:09:13.760 --> 00:09:14.640
as we call it.

00:09:14.640 --> 00:09:16.320
Where it come out from:

00:09:16.320 --> 00:09:22.880
One is the cranium, from where we have
the middle part of the brain,

00:09:22.880 --> 00:09:26.800
the midbrain, from where
the nerves come out.

00:09:26.800 --> 00:09:30.480
From where also, one of the cranial nerves
is the vagus nerve,

00:09:30.480 --> 00:09:34.240
which comprises the major part
of the parasympathetic nervous system

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:36.480
that innervates all the organs.

00:09:36.480 --> 00:09:39.840
And then you have the sacral outflow.

00:09:39.840 --> 00:09:44.640
So, you have the cranio-sacral outflow.

00:09:44.640 --> 00:09:49.600
So, there are two sources of outflows,
but there is nothing in between.

00:09:49.600 --> 00:09:53.360
And that, to me at least,
is very interesting

00:09:53.360 --> 00:09:57.200
from a correlation point of view
of that gap

00:09:57.200 --> 00:09:59.920
in the parasympathetic nervous system.

00:09:59.920 --> 00:10:03.760
That there is the cranial outflow
and there is the sacral outflow,

00:10:03.760 --> 00:10:05.120
but there is nothing in between.

00:10:05.120 --> 00:10:06.880
It doesn't mean there are no nerves.

00:10:06.880 --> 00:10:07.600
There are nerves.

00:10:07.600 --> 00:10:10.080
The vagus does innervate it.

00:10:10.080 --> 00:10:14.560
But that gap, to me,
corresponds to the Void.

00:10:14.560 --> 00:10:19.040
So, the Void is not that
there is nothing there.

00:10:19.040 --> 00:10:23.520
The Void is a way
of communicating

00:10:23.520 --> 00:10:27.680
that there is this gap
in the parasympathetic nervous system,

00:10:27.680 --> 00:10:31.440
and that gap needs to be
bridged, if you will.

00:10:31.440 --> 00:10:34.320
So, once again, in the subtle system,
there is a dot, dot, dot,

00:10:34.320 --> 00:10:36.240
it's kind of a dotted line
from the second

00:10:36.240 --> 00:10:38.800
to the fourth energy center,
with the third energy center

00:10:38.800 --> 00:10:40.000
coming in between.

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:45.440
And that corresponds
to the spiritual anatomy,

00:10:45.440 --> 00:10:49.920
and, maybe, the neuroanatomy
of the nervous system.

00:10:49.920 --> 00:10:53.040
That said, back to the
enteric nervous system.

00:10:53.040 --> 00:10:58.320
The enteric nervous system
contains as many neurons -

00:10:58.320 --> 00:10:59.600
hold your breath -

00:10:59.600 --> 00:11:04.640
as many neurons as there are
neurons in the spinal cord.

00:11:04.640 --> 00:11:09.520
So, you literally have billions
of neurons in the gut.

00:11:09.520 --> 00:11:13.120
And that's why the gut,
the enteric nervous system,

00:11:13.120 --> 00:11:15.760
is now referred to as
the second brain.

00:11:15.760 --> 00:11:20.960
We have the brain, and now this is
considered increasingly as the second brain,

00:11:20.960 --> 00:11:26.080
which is why gut health,
the microbiome, the microbiota,

00:11:26.080 --> 00:11:29.040
there's trillions of bacteria
that live in our gut

00:11:29.040 --> 00:11:32.800
that have been in existence with us
since we started

00:11:32.800 --> 00:11:41.040
our evolutionary journey. All of this
controls our mood, our emotions,

00:11:41.040 --> 00:11:42.640
how we feel.

00:11:42.640 --> 00:11:44.480
We eat good food, we feel good.

00:11:44.480 --> 00:11:48.080
If we are dyspeptic, if we are feeling
something, nauseated,

00:11:48.080 --> 00:11:49.840
that also impacts our mood.

00:11:49.840 --> 00:11:56.160
So, increasingly, there is an understanding
that the enteric nervous system,

00:11:56.160 --> 00:12:00.320
or the region that
corresponds to the Void,

00:12:00.320 --> 00:12:03.840
has an effect on our brain.

00:12:03.840 --> 00:12:06.720
It controls our mood,
it controls our emotion,

00:12:06.720 --> 00:12:10.080
it manages our immune system as well.

00:12:10.080 --> 00:12:13.600
A lot of, for example,
inflammatory bowel disease

00:12:13.600 --> 00:12:16.800
or those kinds of diseases
are now known to have

00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:21.440
that psychosomatic relationship,
that inflammatory component.

00:12:21.440 --> 00:12:24.400
So, there is a very sophisticated
immune system

00:12:24.400 --> 00:12:26.320
that exists within the gut as well.

00:12:26.320 --> 00:12:32.080
So, all of this comes together to form
what may be called the Void,

00:12:32.080 --> 00:12:34.640
or is called, from the spiritual
point of view, the Void,

00:12:34.640 --> 00:12:40.080
but it is anything but empty,
and it has a very important role to play

00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:42.240
in our spiritual journey.

00:12:42.240 --> 00:12:45.920
So, the third energy center,
which is called the Manipura chakra

00:12:45.920 --> 00:12:51.680
or the Nabhi chakra,
governs, from a Sahaj point of view,

00:12:51.680 --> 00:12:58.320
the action of a very well-known plexus
called the solar plexus.

00:12:58.320 --> 00:13:03.120
The solar plexus, in anatomy,
is actually called the celiac plexus,

00:13:03.120 --> 00:13:06.960
and it is situated here,
between the umbilicus

00:13:06.960 --> 00:13:11.760
and the lower part of the sternum,
but at the back of the body,

00:13:11.760 --> 00:13:18.080
just behind the structures
that lie there,

00:13:18.080 --> 00:13:21.280
and it is called the solar plexus
because, if you look at it,

00:13:21.280 --> 00:13:23.600
it looks like a sun
with kind of nerves

00:13:23.600 --> 00:13:25.440
radiating from it,

00:13:25.440 --> 00:13:32.640
and the celiac plexus,
has a number of sub-plexuses,

00:13:32.640 --> 00:13:39.440
and those plexuses control
the functioning of the organs

00:13:39.440 --> 00:13:44.560
that are, quote-unquote, very, 
very, very important or very critical.

00:13:44.560 --> 00:13:47.360
Everything is important,
but even more so,

00:13:47.360 --> 00:13:50.960
the liver, the pancreas, the spleen.

00:13:50.960 --> 00:13:54.480
The hepatic plexus has innervations,
which is the sub-plexus

00:13:54.480 --> 00:13:55.760
of the celiac plexus.

00:13:55.760 --> 00:14:00.640
It looks after the functioning of the liver
or is involved with that functioning.

00:14:00.640 --> 00:14:04.160
Similarly, the pancreatic plexus
and the spleen plexus,

00:14:04.160 --> 00:14:08.000
and the upper part of the gut,
which is the stomach, the duodenum,

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:09.680
the jejunum, and so on and so forth.

00:14:09.680 --> 00:14:16.160
So, again, as I said before,
the second energy center,

00:14:16.160 --> 00:14:18.560
and the third energy center,

00:14:18.560 --> 00:14:22.000
which is the Swadhisthana 
and the Nabhi and the Void.

00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:25.840
These three together, which is why
we are covering them today

00:14:25.840 --> 00:14:27.440
in this episode,

00:14:27.440 --> 00:14:33.440
look after the functioning
of the entire organ systems,

00:14:33.440 --> 00:14:36.480
including the reproductive system,
the excretory system,

00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:38.400
the kidneys, for example.

00:14:38.400 --> 00:14:42.640
They are all governed
between these two energy centers,

00:14:42.640 --> 00:14:46.640
through their innervations.

00:14:48.480 --> 00:14:54.160
This might be a great opportunity also
to understand in a very brief,

00:14:54.160 --> 00:14:57.360
like a few, couple of minutes, literally.

00:14:57.360 --> 00:15:03.360
A couple of organs in the body
that are also important

00:15:03.360 --> 00:15:06.480
from a spiritual point of view,
in a different way.

00:15:06.480 --> 00:15:10.400
It's somewhat absurd to say
that only some organs are more important

00:15:10.400 --> 00:15:12.080
than others. That's not the point.

00:15:12.080 --> 00:15:13.840
What we are trying to say
is a little different.

00:15:13.840 --> 00:15:16.720
So, let's take the case
of the liver, for example.

00:15:16.720 --> 00:15:21.920
Now, the liver is considered
a vital organ in the body,

00:15:21.920 --> 00:15:24.080
much like the heart, the brain,
and the kidneys.

00:15:24.080 --> 00:15:28.080
The liver is critical; it has
a number of functions,

00:15:28.080 --> 00:15:32.800
but one of the most important functions,
along with the fact that it produces bile

00:15:32.800 --> 00:15:36.160
and it helps
in the digestion of fat.

00:15:36.160 --> 00:15:39.600
It stores the other form of glucose,
that is, glycogen.

00:15:39.600 --> 00:15:42.960
It has that, but the liver
also detoxifies.

00:15:42.960 --> 00:15:48.000
It has a very important function
in the sense that whatever food we eat,

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:52.080
the nutrients that are absorbed
from the gut first pass

00:15:52.080 --> 00:15:53.200
through the liver.

00:15:53.200 --> 00:15:56.160
It's called the hepatic portal system,

00:15:56.160 --> 00:16:01.600
and it is where a lot of toxins
are destroyed.

00:16:01.600 --> 00:16:05.280
So, the liver is like
your detoxification center,

00:16:05.280 --> 00:16:09.120
apart from its
other aspects.

00:16:09.120 --> 00:16:13.440
As the founder of this
system of meditation,

00:16:13.440 --> 00:16:20.480
Shri Mataji has said that the Void
is reflective of the ocean,

00:16:20.480 --> 00:16:24.240
and why that is so,
and of the principle of the master.

00:16:24.240 --> 00:16:28.800
And the reason why that is so
is that the ocean is something

00:16:28.800 --> 00:16:35.440
that takes in all of our toxins
and purifies them,

00:16:35.440 --> 00:16:39.840
and it is sent back to us
in the form of clouds

00:16:39.840 --> 00:16:42.000
and then rain, and so on and so forth.

